ury pharmacists  small group discussions are held on each campus and led by in person faculty who facilitate student interaction  discussion  and understanding of the material on experience to help our students as they provide patient care through our experiential curriculum  starting in their first semester of pharmacy school Our Rockford campus is part of the UIC Health Sciences Campus  home to the UIC College of Medicine and College of Nursing in Rockford  Rockford is the fourth largest city in Illinois and offers a small city feel for students who may prefer this recognized Anderson Japanese Gardens  Pharmacy student organizations  professional fraternities  and clubs are all available to choose from as you develop into an excellent and caring pharmacist Anderson Japanese Gardens For students interested in practicing in a rural community upon graduation the Rockford Campus offers the Rural Pharmacy Education Program  RPHARM  students in the RPHARM Program are recognized as having completed a concentration in rural pharmacy services RMED  and Rural Nursing Program  RNURSING The UIC College of Pharmacy at Chicago and Rockford offer students a top tier nationally ranked pharmacy education  students will benefit from faculty who have an open door policy and pride themselves on great student mentorship and guidance  close knit student and faculty community  opportunities for interprofessional activities  and a lower cost of living are perfect for students considering a premier UIC College of Pharmacy education with these added bonuses Plan to visit us and learn more about the Rockford Campus  visit us Sincerely  n r nDr  Kevin O  Rynn  PharmD  FCCP  DABAT r nVice Dean and Clinical Professor Rockford Campus Address       Parkview Ave Rm A    Rockford  IL       Phone               Fax                nRequest Information About the Rockford Campus Register for a PharmD Information Session  Request Information About the Rockford Campus Register for a PharmD Information Se